# Grind — Coffee for Students & Hustlers

A coffee shop landing page and menu built for late nights, deep focus, and the kind of quiet that gets things done.

## Tech Stack

- **Laravel 13** — backend framework
- **Livewire v4** — fullstack components with SPA navigation
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — utility-first styling with custom design tokens
- **Vite 8** — asset bundling

## Project Structure

Follows a team-standard **Livewire Pages** architecture — every page section is its own Livewire component, even static ones.

```
app/Livewire/Pages/
├── Home/
│   ├── Index.php        ← Orchestrator (thin)
│   ├── Hero.php
│   ├── Features.php
│   ├── Menu.php
│   ├── Cta.php
│   └── Contact.php      ← Interactive: form + mail
└── Menu/
    ├── Index.php        ← Orchestrator (thin)
    ├── Hero.php
    ├── Categories.php
    └── Cta.php
```

**Why full-Livewire even for static sections?**
- Any section can gain reactivity later without a refactor
- Sections can be lazy-loaded for free (`<livewire:pages.home.hero lazy />`)
- Clean separation: one PHP file for logic, one Blade file for markup

## Features

- SPA navigation via `wire:navigate.hover` — page transitions without full reloads
- Scroll-aware navbar — transparent on top, dark on scroll
- Contact form with Laravel Mail (`ContactMail` Mailable)
- Google Maps embed for Bacnotan, La Union
- Full menu page with categorized drink cards
- Centralized design tokens in `app.css` — one source of truth for brand colors and fonts
- Responsive layout — mobile and desktop

